reviews_data.review_text:
Giddy Goat is hands down one of the best coffee shops in Charlotte! The vibes here are absolutely amazing—every time I walk in, I’m greeted with smiles and genuine warmth. The coffee is exceptional, with beans roasted right in the shop, and you can even watch the process happen.

But it doesn’t stop at coffee—the empanadas are made fresh daily and are absolutely to die for. Whether you’re stopping in for a quick bite or settling in for a work session, the setup is perfect. Their co-working space invites people from all over the city to connect, collaborate, and create. And if you prefer to soak in the energy of Plaza Midwood, their outdoor seating is the perfect spot to enjoy a cup of coffee while watching the hustle and bustle of the neighborhood.

I also love their “depot spot” inside the Dowd YMCA, making it easy to grab a quality cup of coffee after a workout and before heading to work.

The ownership team is phenomenal—you can tell they are not just passionate about coffee but also deeply committed to their customers. They have truly created a space that blends community, quality, and comfort in the best way possible.

Highly recommend checking out Giddy Goat—you won’t be disappointed!

I had a bad experience today as they give extremely hot coffee without lids. At the time of giving me the boiling coffee, one of their employees pushed me by accident and burnt me with this super hot liquid. Nobody helped me from the staff just a couple of customers that saw the whole situation. The staff were careless about this. Later on I spoke to someone  that he said he is a manager and requested that please take this accident as a learning experience as when handing coffee to customers please put lids on all the time to avoid situations like this in the future. Hopefully this will change ASAP for the benefit of all of the clients of this place to avoid things that can be definitely controlled

If you haven't visited Giddy Goat yet.. this is your sign to immediately run not walk and head over there. They have the best food and pastries. Coffee is delicious. I asked for a big catering order and they were eager to help! I am so happy we went with them. And Gabe who made the order the morning before --- what a gem. He was so kind and efficient. Helped me to my car with everything. Double checked the order with me. Really made the experience stand out. Thank you Giddy Goat!

My fiance and I came here yesterday. All their coffees only come in one size. I got the dirty chai iced and it was okay. My fiance got a hot cappuccino. The barista didn't ask him how he would like it (wet/dry) and when he got it, his cup wasn't even full. He was dissaponted.
We also got the empanadas, which were delicious. The caprice one was bomb especially with the chimchurri. However, everything we got was not worth the $25 we spent.
Beautiful pastries and great vibe. You can see the roaster!

I am not sure why everyone is going crazy for the place. I should have known when I saw a guy outside the coffee shop drinking a Starbucks. I ordered an ICED coffee, and it was hot. The ice in the cup the cup was melted as soon as I got it. You have to prepare your coffee yourself. The sugar shaker is wet at the top, so the sugar does not come out. Again, the section to prepare your coffee is filthy. The girl at the girl at the counter is rude. Do yourself a favor and go Starbucks next door.

reviews_data.review_text: The Giddy Goat Coffee Roasters is a hidden gem for coffee enthusiasts. Their meticulously crafted roasts showcase a perfect balance of flavor and aroma, whether you’re savoring a bright cup of drip coffee  or a rich, chocolatey espresso blend. Each cup bursts with freshness, a testament to their dedication to quality and roasting. The cozy, welcoming vibe of their café complements the exceptional coffee, making it an ideal spot to linger or grab a quick pick-me-up. Friendly baristas and attention to detail in every brew make The Giddy Goat a must-visit for anyone seeking a truly elevated coffee experience.
Best coffee shop in CLT. The food is delicious and the lattes are consistently delicious.
Delicious quality food. Great friendly hard working staff. Clean eating area.

We recently visited Charlotte for an overnight trip for the first time. Of course we googled top rated coffee shops in the area and The Giddy Goat caught my eye! The reviews were super good and the menu looked perfectly simple. The staff was very friendly and shop was warm and cozy. We went on a rainy, cold morning so it was a perfect place to go to. We both got iced vanilla lattes, despite it being 30 degrees outside, and they were so delicious!! You could really taste the fresh coffee bean flavor and it was a super yummy tasting coffee. I’m not a coffee connoisseur and I usually don’t like the taste of actual coffee, whoever, this changed my mind on liking that robust flavor with my sweet latte!! I was very impressed!! My boyfriend got the empanadas for a snack and he said they were absolutely delicious as well. He crushed them! If I were to go back to Charlotte, I would for sure stop here again! It seemed like a local hotspot too!
I just discovered the Giddy Goat and already know it will be a new favorite place to go.

Rude, rude, rude. This place is the unfriendliest place to have a cup of coffee. A popular place can get busy, I get it. But that's no excuse for being unwelcoming. I ordered an empanada the size slightly larger than a tortellini, that was $4. My friend also ordered an empanada, which was much larger. I inquired why mine was sizably smaller and was told that they used a different "fold". The attitude was sort of like, whatever do you want the empanada? I've got to get to my next customer. First of all, how do you charge someone the same amount for less food. This reminds of the Robert De Niro scene in the movie Casino where he required every blueberry muffin to have the exact same amount of blueberries. Secondly, the attitude and vibe is all wrong. Needless to say, I will never visit this establishment again. Back to friendlier water at Undercurrent.

I decided to give this place another try, hoping my first visit was just an off day. Unfortunately, the experience didn’t improve much. The coffee was overly acidic and had a burnt flavor, making it far from enjoyable. The matcha was incredibly disappointing—essentially tasteless, like drinking green-colored milk. The empanadas and pastry were mediocre at best, nothing memorable or worth recommending.

That said, the service was above average, and the staff were friendly and attentive, which was a bright spot in the visit. The general atmosphere inside was also pleasant and welcoming, but sadly, the quality of the food and drinks just didn’t match the ambiance. It’s a decent spot for the vibe, but the menu leaves much to be desired.

This has become my favorite coffee shop in Charlotte. I’ve tried nearly all of them, and this one takes the cake for me. I’ve been here a few times now, and have had multiple different drinks, and they’re all great. Recently, I had a Vietnamese cold brew here, and it quite literally is my favorite cup of coffee i’ve ever had. Super light and creamy, it had a similar experience to drinking a beer as it had a head and a base, it was phenomenal. I’ve also had a couple scones from here and they were great, I can’t speak for the empanadas as I haven’t tried them, but they look great. Overall, this place has all 5 stars for me. Great atmosphere, one of the best for coffee shops in the area, and the coffee is the best in my opinion. This is my go to for coffee, and you should try it too, you won’t be disappointed.

Giddy Goat is hands down one of the best coffee shops in Charlotte! The vibes here are absolutely amazing—every time I walk in, I’m greeted with smiles and genuine warmth. The coffee is exceptional, with beans roasted right in the shop, and you can even watch the process happen.

But it doesn’t stop at coffee—the empanadas are made fresh daily and are absolutely to die for. Whether you’re stopping in for a quick bite or settling in for a work session, the setup is perfect. Their co-working space invites people from all over the city to connect, collaborate, and create. And if you prefer to soak in the energy of Plaza Midwood, their outdoor seating is the perfect spot to enjoy a cup of coffee while watching the hustle and bustle of the neighborhood.

I also love their “depot spot” inside the Dowd YMCA, making it easy to grab a quality cup of coffee after a workout and before heading to work.

The ownership team is phenomenal—you can tell they are not just passionate about coffee but also deeply committed to their customers. They have truly created a space that blends community, quality, and comfort in the best way possible.

Highly recommend checking out Giddy Goat—you won’t be disappointed!

I had a bad experience today as they give extremely hot coffee without lids. At the time of giving me the boiling coffee, one of their employees pushed me by accident and burnt me with this super hot liquid. Nobody helped me from the staff just a couple of customers that saw the whole situation. The staff were careless about this. Later on I spoke to someone  that he said he is a manager and requested that please take this accident as a learning experience as when handing coffee to customers please put lids on all the time to avoid situations like this in the future. Hopefully this will change ASAP for the benefit of all of the clients of this place to avoid things that can be definitely controlled

If you haven't visited Giddy Goat yet.. this is your sign to immediately run not walk and head over there. They have the best food and pastries. Coffee is delicious. I asked for a big catering order and they were eager to help! I am so happy we went with them. And Gabe who made the order the morning before --- what a gem. He was so kind and efficient. Helped me to my car with everything. Double checked the order with me. Really made the experience stand out. Thank you Giddy Goat!

We also got the empanadas, which were delicious. The caprice one was bomb especially with the chimchurri. However, everything we got was not worth the $25 we spent.

reviews_data.review_text: The Giddy Goat Coffee Roasters is a hidden gem for coffee enthusiasts. Each cup bursts with freshness, a testament to their dedication to quality and roasting. The cozy, welcoming vibe of their café complements the exceptional coffee, making it an ideal spot to linger or grab a quick pick-me-up. Friendly baristas and attention to detail in every brew make The Giddy Goat a must-visit for anyone seeking a truly elevated coffee experience.

We recently visited Charlotte for an overnight trip for the first time. Of course we googled top rated coffee shops in the area and The Giddy Goat caught my eye! The reviews were super good and the menu looked perfectly simple. The staff was very friendly and shop was warm and cozy. We went on a rainy, cold morning so it was a perfect place to go to. We both got iced vanilla lattes, despite it being 30 degrees outside, and they were so delicious!! You could really taste the fresh coffee bean flavor and it was a super yummy tasting coffee. I’m not a coffee connoisseur and I usually don’t like the taste of actual coffee, whoever, this changed my mind on liking that robust flavor with my sweet latte!! I was very impressed!! My boyfriend got the empanadas for a snack and he said they were absolutely delicious as well. He crushed them! If I were to go back to Charlotte, I would for sure stop here again! I ordered an empanada the size slightly larger than a tortellini, that was $4. My friend also ordered an empanada, which was much larger. I inquired why mine was sizably smaller and was told that they used a different "fold". The attitude was sort of like, whatever do you want the empanada? I've got to get to my next customer. The empanadas and pastry were mediocre at best, nothing memorable or worth recommending.

This has become my favorite coffee shop in Charlotte. I’ve tried nearly all of them, and this one takes the cake for me. I tend to be quite picky about coffee, as lots of cafes in the area often leave me disappointed, but not Giddy Goat. I’ve been here a few times now, and have had multiple different drinks, and they’re all great. Recently, I had a Vietnamese cold brew here, and it quite literally is my favorite cup of coffee i’ve ever had. Super light and creamy, it had a similar experience to drinking a beer as it had a head and a base, it was phenomenal. I’ve also had a couple scones from here and they were great, I can’t speak for the empanadas as I haven’t tried them, but they look great. Overall, this place has all 5 stars for me. Great atmosphere, one of the best for coffee shops in the area, and the coffee is the best in my opinion. This is my go to for coffee, and you should try it too, you won’t be disappointed.

Giddy Goat is a wonderful addition to the commonwealth. It is consistently slammed!

Cons: parking. The parking sucks. Since it's always busy here the parking lot is regularly full. Furthermore... the empanadas. The flavor is on point. I've tried every empanada and honestly I love them but sometimes I can't get past the raw dough in the middle and on the bottom. They need a minimum of another 5 minutes in the oven since they aren't fried. Check the bottoms! I would love to see the crust a more golden brown across the entire pastry and not just a few spots on the top.

Pros: coffee! Love that they roast their own coffee. It's delicious. The staff that serves it up is always polite, personable, and kind. The overall environment at giddy goat is amazing. A great sense of community. You can tell that people love coming here. The atmosphere is perfect for meet ups, business, college students, family. I also love that GG does coffee and workouts, yoga and coffee, and dance lessons. There's also live music almost every week and tons of local art for sale.

I come here regularly and will continue to do so. As soon as I see those empanadas not as raw.. the 5th star will come.

I wish y'all great business!
